This paper presents a framework for generating robust biped locomotion, which is a common topic in robotics research. The paper focuses on the control aspect of the framework, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses the concept of Divergent Component of Motion (DCM), which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) research. The paper also mentions the use of a Linear-Quadratic-Gaussian (LQG) controller, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) research. Finally, the paper uses simulations to validate the proposed framework, which suggests that it may also fall under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
